    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Mapping SR24 dynamics</prj:name>
        <prj:note>Our goal is to map SR24's surface brightness in gas and dust emission in band7 (resolution 0.12 arcsec). Emission line gas data will provide spectroscopy with a resolution of about 0.1 kms/s. This will reveal (or not) the mass transfer between the two stellar systems. It will also allow us to compare the radial velocities of the two stars. On the other hand, the axis ratio of the disks will inform us on disk inclination angles, which will tell whether the disks lie co-planar with each other, or not. This information is key to enable a spatial reconstruction of the whole interaction picture in three dimensions, and also the true kinematical scenarios.
We aim to also measure the gas rotating at sub-Keplerian speeds. 
Another goal that will be achieved with this setup is the detection of the continuum disk around SR24N (which has been previously detected in 12CO gas).
</prj:note>
