        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We request Band 7, array C34-7 (most extended configuration), HCO+(4-3) 356.73Hz and 12CO(3-2) 345.79GHz plus continuum observations.
Both disks are bright in CO gas. The SR24S velocity-integrated (∆v = 2 km/s) line has an intensity of 4 K km/s. A much stronger line is seen in SR24N with a velocity integrated intensity of 17 K km/s. Both disks have about 2-3” sizes. The SR24S disk has a mass of 0.01 M⊙, while the northern disk is about a Jupiter mass (assuming T = 30 K and an opacity of 0.02 cm2/g). To detect the northern dust disk we need sensitivities of a hundredth of a Jupiter mass (assuming gas/dust = 100), or 8 mJy. The OT sensitivity calculator yields a 10-sigma detection with 40min on source, 1.9 hr including overheads.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
